Package core

Interface HlaHLAobjectRootManager

  • public interface HlaHLAobjectRootManager
    Manager used to manage HlaHLAobjectRoots.

    This class is ThreadSafe as defined by Java Concurrency in Practice, see jcip.net.

      • addHlaHLAobjectRootDefaultInstanceListener

        void addHlaHLAobjectRootDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaHLAobjectRootListener listener)
        Add a listener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaHLAobjectRoot (Both local and remote). The listener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaHLAobjectRoot is updated. The listener is also called when an interaction is sent to an instance of HlaHLAobjectRoot. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to add.

      • removeHlaHLAobjectRootDefaultInstanceListener

        void removeHlaHLAobjectRootDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaHLAobjectRootListener listener)
        Remove a listener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaHLAobjectRoot. Note: The listener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaHLAobjectRoot. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to remove.

      • addHlaHLAobjectRootDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void addHlaHLAobjectRootDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaHLAobjectRootValueListener valueListener)
        Add a valueListener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaHLAobjectRoot (Both local and remote). The Valuelistener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaHLAobjectRoot is updated. Note that the attribute values that are notified are not guaranteed to be the latest available values for that attribute. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to add.

      • removeHlaHLAobjectRootDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void removeHlaHLAobjectRootDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaHLAobjectRootValueListener valueListener)
        Remove a valueListener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaHLAobjectRoot. Note: The valueListener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaHLAobjectRoot. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to remove.

      • setEnabled

        void setEnabled​(boolean enabled)
        Enables or disables the HlaHLAobjectRoot manager. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaHLAobjectRoot manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable the HlaHLAobjectRoot manager, otherwise false

      • setEnabledIfAvailableInFom

        void setEnabledIfAvailableInFom()
        Enables the HlaHLAobjectRoot manager if it is available in the FOM at runtime. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaHLAobjectRoot manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Check if the HlaHLAobjectRoot manager is actually enabled when connected. An HlaHLAobjectRoot manager may be disabled with the setEnabled(false) function, or it may be configured as if available in the FOM by the setEnabledIfAvailableInFom() function and then not available in the FOM at runtime.

        This method should only be used when connected, it will always return false when not connected.

        Returns:
        true if connected and the HlaHLAobjectRoot manager is enabled.
